This is NOT one of the more common Spanish made La Coruna M43 rifles."S/42G" marked rear sight, "lxr" marked magazine follower. Bolt, trigger-guard, floor-plate and receiver are all matching, other parts are un-numbered, as is correct for these rifles. Shiny and prominent Spanish Airforce eagle crest stamped center of receiver. Maintains 95% original bluing, walnut stock is in good condition except for small crack above rear stock plate. These are all scarce and desirable items that are worth it by themselves. This rifle is very difficult to find with all its' original accessories along with being in the condition that it is. This rifle is meant for collector's specifically Mauser enthusiasts, it has a lot of history behind it especially if you have read "Homage to Catalonia" by George Orwell. Made for Spanish military, high quality military craftsmanship unlike the common M43 Spanish Mausers which had heat treatment issues. $1500

This rifle is beautifully made (pre-WWI build quality and attention to detail was absolutely superb) and is nicely marked with the Peruvian crest on the receiver partially removed, under which is marked "MAUSER ORIGINAL". This rifle is completely original.It is NOT import marked. The original blue finish rates about 80%. The stock is in very good shape with handling wear no cracks or chips...and never sanded or refinished. The mechanics are in good working order and the bore is sharp and bright. title: For Sale:  Kar98k with Nikon 3-9x40 Prostaff Scope
postcontent:
For sale is a Kar98k in good to very good condition.  The rifle appears to have been arsenal refurbished at some point judging by the mixed proof marks.  While the wood has definitely seen better days, the metal is still in great shape, with strong rifling, an undamaged crown, and tight action.  Of particular interest is that the receiver appears to be a pre-war model manufactured in Czechoslovakia at BRNO.  The action is, as Mausers are known for, buttery smooth.  This rifle will do 1.5 MOA at 100 yards with Prvi Partizan 8mm all day long and I have no reason to think it wouldn't do so at longer ranges.

Included with this rifle is a Nikon Prostaff scope with BDC reticle.  It is a 3-9 power scope with a 40mm objective lens.  It is a very crisp and clear scope in nearly new condition.  I'm even including the box the scope came in if you want it.

The scope is mounted with an S&K no-drill mount.  This is a very secure mount that reliably holds zero without having to drill into the receiver, a very nice feature on guns like the Kar98k that have very hard steel used in their receivers.  It does necessitate a small amount of inletting on the stock, however.

Lastly, this offer includes a supply of ammo and reloading components to get you going.  40 rounds of Prvi Partizan 8x57, 25 rounds of Sellier & Bellot 8x57, 100 ct Sierra Pro-Hunter 150 gr spitzer .323 bullets, a set of Lee carbide reloading dies for 8mm Mauser, and 95 cartridge cases ready to reload.  Note, pictured but not included are 3 green reusable ammo cases.

You get all of this for $500.  That's $400 for the rifle, $100 for the scope, and the mount, ammo, and reloading supplies are free.

title: For Sale:  Swiss K31 with Ammo and stripper clips
postcontent:
For sale is a Swiss K31 carbine in very good condition.  This rifle features the walnut stock in exceptionally good condition.  K31s are infamous for having beautifully maintained metal and roughly used wood; this model has both excellent condition metal and a very good condition stock.  It has a small amount of water damage at the buttplate, but it extends barely an inch into the wood.  Under the buttplate can be found the traditional name and contact information for the soldier to whom it was issued.  It must have served him well, for it had earned itself a name at some point in its life: Miss Liddy.  This is a 1 MOA gun.  Yes, with irons.  It is a beautiful bit of workmanship with a crisp 2 stage, 3 lb trigger.

Also in this package, you will get 87 rounds of GP-11 surplus ammunition.  This is non-reloadable, non-corrosive Swiss surplus and the K31 loves it.  You also get 40 rounds of 7.5x55 Swiss Prvi Partizan.  This is reloadable ammunition and also very accurate in this rifle.  Lastly, you get two of the proper waxed cardboard stripper clips.  These are hard to find due to their material, but this pair is still in very good condition.

This rifle alone, when you can find it, goes for $350.  This rifle and all its accessories can be yours for just $300!
REDACTED

Often referred to as the "Pocket Glock" or "Baby Glock," the Glock 26 debuted in 1995 as the perfect concealed carry pistol. Only about six and half inches long and four inches tall, the Glock 26 is simple and lightweight in a conceal carry holster. Backed by the quality and history of excellence carried by Glock, the Glock 26 remains a popular subcompact semi-automatic pistol nearly 20 years after its debut and is primarily used by civilians interested in concealed carry.

The Glock 26's size only allows for a two-finger pistol grip but its double-stacked magazine still carries ten rounds of 9mm ammunition. Not just a smaller version of its predecessors, the Glock 26 was created through an extensive redesign of the frame, spring assembly and locking block. Featuring no less than three independent safety systems, the Glock line utilizes two internal, automatic safeties as well as an external integrated trigger safety. The internal mechanisms are comprised of both a drop safety and a firing pin safety. Once the trigger is squeezed, the three safety mechanisms are automatically disengaged one after the other. When the trigger is released, they automatically reactivate.

They also limit the number of boxes you can buy. Incidentally, these were well known retailers and not entities that just popped up for the short term.
 I prefer not to sell it, but would rather trade it for Federal Champion 36 grain copper plated 22LR, or I'd even consider trading for Remington Golden Bullets 22LR. That way I won't have to spend the next 6-8 months trying to replace it.
 If you want a good 22LR cartridge that will cycle your semi-auto properly without gumming it up, this is it! Make a trade or buy it outright. (trades preferred)
 Trades would be: one box of FEDERAL AUTO MATCH for one box Federal Champion in either the 525 blue or 550 red box. Or, one box of auto match for one 525 round box of Remington Golden bullets 22LR.
